Very good on sandwiches--the taste recalls the relish on New Orleans muffuletta sandwiches. Not so good if you're pressed for time, since there's a lot of chopping and mixing (also, it's better to make it a day or two ahead to give the flavors time to ripen). Everybody loves it, and dieters are especially grateful. Great stuff!

Rating: 4
My daughter is a vegan and I make this every time she visits. It lasts in the refrigerator for days and even freezes well. Full of robust flavor. For speed I have used the fresh-frozen cubes of garlic, basil and parsley. The outcome was an even more robust flavor, but a slightly less red, more green color.

Rating: 3
This is a great relish/spread for vegetables and bread alike. I had a Mediterranean dinner last night and used this as my main appetizer - everyone loved it. I had a number of vegetables and some toasted focaccia (which I preferred). My husband wants me to make him a sandwich for lunch today with the leftovers. Definitely a keeper with or without other Mediterranean dishes.

